==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: flywheel
<hw>flywheel</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A heavy wheel or disk which stores
kinetic energy by rotating on a shaft, and by its momentum smoothes the
operation of a reciprocating engine by reducing fluctuations of speed.
It is used in certain types of machinery, such as automobiles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Flywheels rotating at high speed have also been proposed
as a means to store kinetic energy for use as a low-polluting source of
energy in vehicles.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>FM</ent>⟦br⟧
